Santos Aviation limited providers of maintenance and interior refurbishing services for government and privately owned aircraft is to host the first Federal Aviation Administration FAA of the United States repair station in the country A release signed by Engineer Segun Adesanya, General Manager of Santos Aviation, the company will be hosting a diamond-studed lunch featuring FAA part 145 repair station According to Engr Adesanya, the event which will be on Thursday February 24, 2022 will feature keynote address by Capt Hans Kraus Adesanya explained that his agents and employees have professional and technical licenses issued by the FAA of the United States to provide services on American made and American registered aircraft He disclosed that services provided by by Santos include aircraft /airline seat covers upgrade, carpet binding and surging, galleys, lavatory, panels and PSU, others include refurbishing and sewing services He noted that aviation sector in the country has has great potential for growth which will result in more job training for the youth Adesanya remarked that the growth will provide significant opportunities for profitable joint venture relationships for the public and privately Nigerian entities adding that Santos Aviation was very much interested in joint venture relationships